$ Examples for Visual Basic for Application accessing the Windows API: GetWindowRect

`GetWindowRect` can be used to determine the location and dimension of a window.

The following example uses → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples/ShellExecute[`ShellExecute`] to create an instance of *notepad*, then finds its
window handle with → development/languages/VBA/Win-API/examples/FindWindow[`FindWindow`] and finally calls `GetWindowRect` to determine the dimensions of notepad.

gh|WinAPI-4-VBA|/examples/GetWindowRect.bas||

